A selection of examples of getting started with OpenMPI, please note that all 
derivative works retain the respective license of their authors.  Everything
else is covered under an Apache License 2.0


Requirements
============

You will need to install (Fedora);
	sudo yum install openmpi openmpi-devel openmpi-libs
	

Building
========

It should just be as straight-forward as running 'make', if you are on a 32-bit
system you will need to change the MPICC macro in the Makefile.
